This is An Android home-screen widget for showing information about the current Mobile Network.

Seeing as its only in beta, I'm the only tester as of yet, and my location, The only Mobile Networks I've fully supported are Irish. These can be expanded upon easily when the widget is fully operational.
[Vodafone ie, 02.ie, Three Ireland, Meteor]

Current features:
Checks if device is in Air-plane mode
Scans for MNC & MCC to identify current Mobile Network.
Displays Mobile Network logo and name on widget.
Widget Updated on touch, to save device battery.

Planned features:
Multiple widget sizes to accommodate new features.
A display to show Mobile Network's signal strength.
A timed (or when visible) update system.
A secondary display when connected to WiFi, showing connection strength and data transfer speeds.

